'''ᱡᱚᱭ ᱠᱤᱥᱟᱱ ᱠᱟᱠᱩᱵᱷᱟᱭ "ᱡᱟᱠᱤ" ᱥᱨᱚᱯᱷ''' (ᱡᱟᱱᱟᱢ ᱑ ᱯᱷᱮᱵᱽᱨᱩᱭᱟᱨᱩ ᱑᱙᱕᱗) ᱫᱚ ᱢᱤᱫ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛᱤᱭᱟ‌. ᱟᱠᱴᱚᱨ ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱱᱩᱭ ᱫᱚ ᱯᱩᱱ ᱜᱮᱞ ᱥᱮᱨᱢᱟ ᱦᱩᱭᱩᱜ ᱠᱟᱱᱟ ᱦᱤᱱᱫᱤ ᱥᱤᱱᱮᱢᱟ ([[ᱵᱚᱞᱤᱣᱩᱰ]]) ᱨᱮ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱟᱨ {{as of|2017|lc=yes}} ([[ᱦᱤᱱᱫᱤ]], [[ᱠᱳᱝᱠᱳᱬᱤ]], [[ᱠᱟᱱᱱᱟᱰᱟ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱰᱟ]], [[ᱢᱚᱨᱟᱴᱷᱤ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱢᱚᱨᱟᱴᱷᱤ]], [[ᱳᱰᱤᱭᱟ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱳᱰᱤᱭᱟ]], [[ᱯᱚᱧᱡᱟᱵᱤ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱯᱚᱧᱡᱟᱵᱤ]], [[ᱵᱮᱝᱜᱚᱞᱤ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱵᱮᱝᱜᱚᱞᱤ]], [[ᱢᱟᱞᱟᱭᱚᱞᱚᱢ]], [[ᱛᱟᱢᱤᱞᱤ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱛᱟᱢᱤᱞᱤ]], [[ᱛᱮᱞᱩᱜᱩ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱛᱮᱞᱩᱜᱩ]], [[ᱵᱷᱚᱡᱽᱯᱳᱨᱤ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱵᱷᱚᱡᱽᱯᱳᱨᱤ]], [[ᱜᱩᱡᱽᱨᱟᱛᱤ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱜᱩᱡᱽᱨᱟᱛᱤ]], ᱟᱨ ᱤᱝᱞᱤᱥ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ ᱠᱚ ᱢᱮᱥᱟ ᱠᱟᱛᱮ) ᱒᱒᱐ ᱠᱷᱚᱱ ᱡᱟ.ᱥᱛᱤ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱠᱚᱨᱮ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟᱭ ᱾ <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/i-still-work-with-my-heart-veteran-actor-jackie-shroff-ians-interview-118102000306_1.html|title=I still work with my heart: Veteran actor Jackie Shroff (IANS Interview)|last=Chakravarty|first=Durga|date=20 October 2018|work=Business Standard India|access-date=4 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{IMDb name|0006763}}</ref> ᱱᱩᱭ ᱫᱚ ᱯᱩᱱᱭᱟ. [[ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ‌ᱯᱷᱮᱭᱟᱨ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ]] ᱫᱟᱜᱲᱮ ᱞᱮᱱᱟᱭ ᱟᱨ ᱥᱟᱶ ᱛᱮ ᱟᱭᱢᱟ ᱠᱷᱟᱴᱚ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱠᱟᱨᱮ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟᱭ ᱾

== ᱱᱤᱡᱮᱨᱟᱜ ᱟᱬᱜᱛ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ ==
ᱡᱟᱠᱤ ᱫᱚ, ᱡᱚᱭ ᱠᱤᱥᱟᱱ ᱠᱟᱠᱩᱵᱷᱟᱭ ᱥᱨᱚᱯᱷ ᱧᱩᱛᱩᱢ ᱛᱮ [[ᱢᱩᱢᱵᱟᱭ]], ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛ ᱫᱤᱥᱚᱢ ᱨᱮ ᱡᱟᱱᱟᱢ ᱞᱮᱱᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱟᱡ ᱵᱟᱵᱟ ᱡᱚᱭ ᱠᱤᱥᱟᱱ ᱠᱟᱠᱟᱵᱷᱟᱭ ᱥᱨᱚᱯᱷ ᱫᱚ ᱜᱩᱡᱽᱨᱟᱛ ᱨᱤᱱᱤᱡ ᱦᱚᱲ ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱟᱨ ᱟᱭᱚ [[ᱛᱩᱨᱠᱤᱥ ᱦᱚᱲ|ᱛᱩᱨᱠ]] ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ [[ᱠᱟᱡᱟᱠᱷᱥᱛᱷᱟᱱ]] ᱨᱤᱱᱤᱡ ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱾<ref name="birthplace"/> ᱠᱟᱡᱟᱠᱷᱥᱛᱷᱟᱱ ᱨᱮ ᱡᱚᱠᱷᱚᱱ ᱦᱩᱯᱠᱟ. ᱢᱟ.ᱨᱤ ᱥᱚᱨᱠᱟᱨ ᱠᱚ ᱵᱚᱫᱚᱞ ᱟ.ᱪᱩᱨᱮᱱᱟ ᱟᱡ ᱢᱟᱢᱚ ᱵᱩᱰᱷᱤ ᱫᱚ ᱟᱡ ᱨᱤᱱ ᱮᱭᱟᱭ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ ᱦᱚᱯᱚᱱ ᱮᱨᱟ ᱥᱟᱶᱛᱮ [[ᱞᱚᱫᱟᱠᱷ]] ᱧᱤᱨ ᱦᱮᱡ ᱞᱮᱱᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱫᱚᱥᱟᱨ ᱛᱮ ᱱᱩᱠᱩ ᱫᱚ [[ᱫᱤᱞᱞᱤ]] ᱠᱷᱚᱱ [[ᱢᱩᱢᱵᱟᱭ]] ᱛᱮᱠᱚ ᱩᱪᱟ.ᱲ ᱞᱮᱱᱟ ᱾<ref name="birthplace"/><ref name="rstv">{{cite AV media |people= |date=19 September 2017 |title=Guftagoo with Jackie Shroff |medium= |language=hi |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ef3zTBkrXI4 |access-date=14 April 2019 |archive-url= |archive-date= |time= |publisher= [[Rajya Sabha TV]]}}</ref> ᱟᱡ ᱵᱟᱵᱟ ᱫᱚ ᱜᱩᱡᱽᱨᱟᱛᱤ ᱚᱲᱟᱜ ᱨᱤᱱᱤᱡ ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱟᱨ ᱱᱩᱠᱩ ᱫᱚ ᱵᱮᱯᱟᱨᱤ ᱠᱟ ᱛᱟᱦᱮᱸ ᱞᱮᱱᱟ ᱾ ᱡᱟᱦᱟᱸᱭᱮᱱ ᱜᱮ ᱡᱟᱠᱤ ᱟᱡ ᱵᱟᱵᱟ ᱫᱚ ᱥᱴᱚᱠ ᱢᱟᱨᱠᱮᱴ ᱨᱮ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱡᱷᱚᱛᱚ ᱯᱩᱭᱥᱟ.ᱭ ᱡᱷᱚᱲᱟ ᱦᱚᱪᱚᱭᱮᱱᱟ ᱟᱨ ᱑᱗ ᱥᱟᱞ ᱩᱢᱮᱨ ᱨᱮ ᱚᱲᱚᱜ ᱮ ᱵᱟ.ᱜᱤ ᱠᱟᱛᱮ ᱧᱤᱨ ᱮᱱᱟ ᱾ ᱟᱡ ᱵᱟᱵᱟ ᱟᱨ ᱟᱭᱚ ᱵᱟᱱᱟᱨ ᱜᱮ ᱠᱷᱟᱴᱚ ᱩᱢᱮᱨ ᱨᱮ ᱜᱮ ᱠᱤᱱ ᱧᱟᱯᱟᱢ ᱯᱮᱱᱟ ᱟᱨ ᱠᱤᱱ ᱵᱟᱯᱞᱟ ᱭᱮᱱᱟ ᱾<ref name="birthplace">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news-interviews/I-am-reckless-Jackie-Shroff/articleshow/34292726.cms|title=I am reckless: Jackie Shroff|publisher=The Times of India|date=28 April 2014|accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref>

As a youngster, he modelled in a few advertisements including Savage perfumes. It was one of his classmates in school who gave Shroff his name "Jackie" and then filmmaker [[Subhash Ghai]] stuck to this name when he launched him in the film ''[[Hero (1983 film)|Hero]]''.<ref name="ht">{{cite news|title=Koffee With Karan: How Jackie Shroff put his house at stake and got it back|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/tv/how-jackie-shroff-put-his-house-at-stake-and-got-it-back/story-ZXvSWj2jk06RyGsp0CtG3K.html|accessdate=27 November 2017|publisher=Hindustan Times|date=16 April 2017}}</ref><ref name="GhaiHeroImp">{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/hero-was-an-important-film-for-me-subhash-ghai-1588815.html|title=Hero Was an Important Film for Me: Subhash Ghai|website=News18|access-date=4 January 2019|date=27 November 2017}}</ref> Shroff regularly revisits his childhood home in Teen Batti.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://t2online.com/entertainment/jackie-shroff-goes-back-to-his-one-room-pad-at-teen-batti-where-he-grew-up/cid/19195|title=Jackie Shroff goes back to his one-room pad at Teen Batti, where he grew up|last=Ghosh|first=Debasmita|date=28 March 2018|website=t2online.com|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=4 January 2019}}</ref>

Shroff married his longtime girlfriend [[Ayesha Dutt]], a model who later became a film producer, on her birthday, 5 June 1987.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiatimes.com/culture/who-we-are/jackie-shroff-and-his-family-secrets-exposed-277826.html|title=Jackie Shroff And His Family Secrets Exposed|date=27 April 2016|website=indiatimes.com}}</ref><ref name="ToI5unknown">{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/5-things-you-did-not-know-about-jackie-shroff/photostory/34333661.cms|title=5 things you did not know about Jackie Shroff|website=The Times of India|access-date=4 January 2019}}</ref> The couple runs a media company Jackie Shroff Entertainment Limited. They jointly owned 10% shares in [[Sony Entertainment Television (India)|Sony TV]] from its launch until 2012, when they sold their stake and ended their 15-year-long association with Sony TV. They have two children, a son, Bollywood actor [[Tiger Shroff]] and daughter, Krishna Shroff.

He is a life member of the International Film And Television Club of [[Asian Academy of Film & Television]].
